-- clikae iTerm2 launcher template. Two placeholders are substituted by
-- lib/commands/app.sh: the SHELL_CMD token becomes the env-prefixed CLI command,
-- and the TITLE token becomes the session name (e.g. claude (work)). The tokens
-- carry @ delimiters that this comment omits, so substitution only touches the
-- two code lines below.
--
-- Uses iTerm2's scripting API: `create window with default profile command`
-- opens a new window running the command, then we name the session.

on run
    tell application "iTerm"
        activate
        set newWindow to (create window with default profile command "@SHELL_CMD@")
        tell current session of newWindow
            set name to "@TITLE@"
        end tell
    end tell
end run
